cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the calculation of determinant and permanent of graphs using $\mathcal{B}$-partitions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves some graph theoretic concepts such as block graphs and signed unicyclic graphs, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
